<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1390289" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rafael_gimenez_cadiz_06052020.jpg?resize=640%2C360&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="360" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rafael_gimenez_cadiz_06052020.jpg?w=1024&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rafael_gimenez_cadiz_06052020.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rafael_gimenez_cadiz_06052020.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rafael_gimenez_cadiz_06052020.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rafael_gimenez_cadiz_06052020.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rafael_gimenez_cadiz_06052020.jpg?resize=200%2C113&amp;ssl=1 200w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Spanish footballer who refused to undergo COVID-19 testing as part of the first phase of the sport’s return to activity has defended his decision and promised to not receive a salary while he boycotts training and matches. While players in the top two divisions returned to training grounds on Wednesday to undergo testing ahead of a planned return to action by June after a two-month halt due to the pandemic, Cadiz’s Rafael Gimenez, known as Fali, stayed home. “I’m scared of infecting someone, that would ruin me and I’m thinking about health before money,” the defender, 26, told Spanish radio station Cadena Ser. “I’m worried about the health of my daughters and my family. I was the first person to say that I will not earn a wage in this period and if even one Euro enters my account I’ll give it back.” Cadiz currently leads Spain’s second division and are well placed to be promoted to La Liga for the first time in 15 years when action resumes in June after being postponed in March due to the pandemic, which has claimed over 26,000 lives in Spain. Vanguard Players at Barcelona and Real Madrid started to undergo coronavirus tests on Wednesday as La Liga clubs planned to return to restricted training ahead of the proposed resumption of the season next month. Barca captain Lionel Messi and France international Antoine Griezmann were among players pictured arriving one by one… May 6, 2020 In "Sports" Barcelona defender Eric Abidal said Thursday he is stalling on a new contract offer from the Spanish giants because he is focusing fully on his health six months after undergoing surgery to remove a liver tumour. September 8, 2011 In "Sports" Football is re-awakening amid the COVID-19 pandemic but the sense of hope at teams which have started training is mixed with worry over whether it might be too soon and the uncertainty of how to keep players safe. On hold since mid-March, many European leagues are hoping to start up… April 24, 2020 In "Sports"